author: wn.com
title: State Senate map proposals divide Northeast Florida in new ways
text: This week the Legislature begins its third special session of 2015 and its fourth attempt to draw constitutionally sound House, Senate and congressional maps since 2012. This time, the state Senate map is the focus. The process is expected to be even more contentious than the congressional redistricting session in August that ended without the House and Senate reaching agreement. read more ...
